{{See|façade}}

==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[façade]] [[:fr:façade|(fr)]]'', from Italian ''[[facciata]]'', a derivation of ''[[faccia]]'' "front", which is derived from Latin ''[[facies]]'' "face"; compare ''[[face]]''.

===Noun===
'''facade'''

# The face of a building, especially the front.
# A [[deceptive]] outward appearance.

====Alternative spellings====
*[[façade]]

